<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-09-25T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-09-25T14:00:00-05:00" n="414" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d414">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1163 Am 3/228: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-09-25T15:00:00-04:00">September 25, 1937—3
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>230. Your 412, September 25, 1 p.m. Although interests concerned are
                            predominately French, in view of the fact that American nationals are
                            endangered, the Department desires that you take action irrespective of
                            whether the French also act.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>